pageContext.claim: “But we are signing tomorrow a health care package that will cover -- I don't know -- some people say 30 percent, people say, 25 percent and some people say, it could be 50 percent. It is going to cover a large percentage of the people that we're talking about.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump oversells the impact of an executive order he planned to sign. The executive order does not have a force in law and the regulations are not specifically tied to the Affordable Care Act. So the impact is uncertain.
